Marsha Blackburn ( R - Tenn . ) , the leading GOP candidate in the race for the Tennessee Senate seat being vacated by Republican Sen. Bob Corker . Trump ’s support will take Blackburn a long way in November . After all , he won 92 of Tennessee 's 95 counties in 2016 . But leading Democratic candidate and former Gov. Phil Bredesen enjoys wide support among the Tennessee constituency . Still , voters who attended the rally revealed where they currently stand in the race , which may surprise some . First , what did Trump say ? Speaking to thousands at Municipal Auditorium , Trump called Bredesen " very liberal " and " an absolute total tool " for Democratic leaders in Congress , according to The Tennessean . " If Bredesen were ever to get elected , he ’d do whatever Chuck [ Schumer ] and Nancy [ Pelosi want ] , " Trump said . " You have to work with Marsha . We have to get the votes . We need the votes .
